1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Vê heftiyê jî em li gundê Xezewiyê ne.
 
This week we are in the village of Ghazawiya.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Gundê Xezewiyê jî nêzîkî Keleha Semanê ye.
 
The village of Ghazawiya is close to the Seman Castle.

3
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Gundê Xezewiyê nîvî misilman e, nîvî êzidî ne.
 
The village of Ghazawiya is half Muslim and half Yezidi.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Di Deşta Cûmê de hatiye avakirin.
 
It was built in the Cuma Plain.

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Di quntara Çiyayê Lêlûn de hatiye avakirin.
 
It was built at the foothills of Mount Lelun.

6
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Dê kî vê heftiyê jî em derbasî gundê Xezewiyê bin.
 
Let's enter the village of Ghazawiya this week.

7
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Merheba stêra.
 
Hello, respected one.

8
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Ya ehlen û sehlen, ehlen û sehlen.
 
Welcome, welcome.

9
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Em te nas bikin.
 
Let's get to know you.

10
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Navê min Îsmet e, ji Xezewiyê, li deşta Cûmê, fêkî didim.
 
My name is Ismet, from Ghazawiya, in the Cuma plain, I
produce fruit.

11
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Spasdarim ji te re û destê we sax bin.
 
Thank you and bless your hands.

12
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Ahlen û sehlen ji te re jî.
 
Welcome to you too.

13
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Îro em li gundê Xezewiyê ne. Em daxwaza ji te bikin.
 
Today we are in the village of Ghazawiya. We want to ask
you.

14
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:32,000
Ya ehlen û sehlen.
 
Welcome.

15
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Gundê Xezewiyê zêdetir çi heye?
 
What does the village of Ghazawiya have the most?

16
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Cem me, ekter tişt hinar e. Sêv in, xox e, fawakî, hirmî,
mişmiş e.
 
For us, the most common thing is pomegranates. There are
apples, peaches, fruits, pears, apricots.

17
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,000
Qudra, alem ev diçînin, gî heye.
 
Vegetables, people plant these, there is everything.

18
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Yanî tu çi bixwazî di deşta Cûmê de heye.
 
Meaning whatever you want is in the Cuma plain.

19
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
Deşta Cûmê ye. Gî heye, elhemdulelah.
 
It is the Cuma plain. Everything is there, thank God.

20
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Av jî nêzîkî we ye, di herika we de?
 
Is water also close to you, flowing near you?

21
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Av nêzîkî me re diherike, û meşrû heye û her yekî di nav
erdê xwe de jî bîr hene, avê paqij jî heye û gî heye.
 
Water flows close to us, and there is a project and everyone
has a well in their land, there is clean water and
everything.

22
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Neha sereke darê hinarê ye?
 
So the main thing is the pomegranate tree?

23
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Hinar.
 
Pomegranate.

24
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Serekeyê Xwecem e. Hinarekî lê fon ji gî rindtir e.
 
The main one is for ourselves. The Lefon pomegranate is the
best of all.

25
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Sê-çar nûw hinarî hene.
 
There are three or four types of pomegranates.

26
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Lefon heye, lefona şêrîn heye, lefona tirş heye.
 
There is Lefon, there is sweet Lefon, there is sour Lefon.

27
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Şêrîn bi du sê nûwan heye. Pir nûw heye.
 
The sweet one has two or three types. There are many types.

28
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Firensî heye. Ev cem ne ko bû, hijdeh sal, ev mintaqeya,
hinarî Firensî, maşeallah ev jî pir pê ye.
 
There is the French one. We've had it for about eighteen
years, in this region, the French pomegranate, mashallah it
is also very abundant.

29
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Rengê xuyî sor e, rind e, li sûkê jî rind e, yanî heye.
 
Its color is red, it is beautiful, it is also good in the
market, so we have it.

30
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:30,000
E, neha te go sereke darê hinarê ye. Çiqas hezar darê hinarê
bi awahî heye?
 
So, you said the main thing is the pomegranate tree. Roughly
how many thousand pomegranate trees are there?

31
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:37,000
E, welleh ku em texmîn bikin, di gundê Xezewiyê de, wekî
150,000 heta 200,000 darê hinarê teqrîbî tê de heye.
 
Well, if we were to guess, in the village of Ghazawiya,
there are approximately 150,000 to 200,000 pomegranate
trees.

32
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Hinar heye.
 
There are pomegranates.

33
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Teqrîben fêkî jî te ku nîvî wî, bi hesibîniyê heye.
 
Approximately the fruits are half of that, if you calculate
it.

34
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Fêkî jî heye. Ev cem alemê, yekî pênc sed darê xwe heye,
yekî hezar darê xwe heye, yekî du sed darê xwe heye, her
yekî heye,
 
There are also fruits. Here among the people, one has five
hundred trees, one has a thousand trees, one has two hundred
trees, everyone has some,

35
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,000
di gundê Xezewiyê de.
 
in the village of Ghazawiya.

36
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Yanî sal, hey e salek karê we heye.
 
So you have work all year round.

37
00:02:54,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Sal û sal e ku we karê me heye. Sal bi sal em wê darê
diqesixînin, em vedidin.
 
Year after year we have work. Year by year we prune that
tree, we trim it.

38
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
Salê sê neqlan, em pîçka jê dikişînin.
 
Three times a year, we pull the shoots from it.

39
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Em vêrê dibêjin pîçik, ev gulîçîlk, vêra dibêjin em jê
dikişînin.
 
We call them shoots here, these small branches, we say we
pull them off.

40
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Karê xwe çewîr e, avdan e, heta belavkirin e... Yanî
teqriben ...
 
Its work is digging, watering, up to distributing... So
approximately...

41
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
te ku bê, nehe meh karê me mustemir heye.
 
So to speak, we have continuous work for nine months.

42
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Sê mehê zivistanî baran lêkir, karê me tunne ye.
 
The three winter months when it rains, we have no work.

43
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Di meha yanzdeh de?
 
In the eleventh month?

44
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Erê, di meha dewan yekê, dewan duduyê yekê tunne. U di yekê
û vir de, di meha yekê de, em dest pê dikin qesixînê.
 
Yes, in the eleventh, twelfth, and first months there is
none. And from the first month onwards, in the first month,
we start pruning.

45
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:32,000
A te dît a min neha ku qesixî dikin.
 
As you saw, we are pruning now.

46
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Em qut dikin di cem me de, em xetê didin, dibin qutik.
 
We cut them here, we make a line, we prune them.

47
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:43,000
Zeytûna dera dikin, em jî dibin qesexe. Wan jî dibin
darvedan.
 
They prune the olives, and we do the pruning here. They also
call it tree trimming.

48
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:44,000
Darvedan heye, her yek bitunekî dibêje.
 
There is tree trimming, everyone says it differently.

49
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:49,000
E, neha pirsa ismet, neha dibêjin Basûtê bi hinarê tê
naskirin.
 
So, now a question Ismet, they say Basuta is known for its
pomegranates.

50
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:55,000
E, çi ferq navbera hinara we û Basûtê ye? Ew nêzîkî hev in
yanî.
 
So, what is the difference between your pomegranates and
Basuta's? They are close to each other.

51
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Xet yek e, gî yek e. Ferq tunne ye bejn me. Hinar mabêna
Basûtê û Xezewiyê û Endarê û Tirindê û Îskayê û Şadêrê, gî
yek e, hinar.
 
The line is the same, everything is the same. There is no
difference between us. The pomegranates between Basuta and
Ghazawiya and Andara and Tirinda and Iska and Shadira, they
are all the same, the pomegranates.

52
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Bes, wêrê avê xuyî heye, mexsefî xwe ye pê nas bûye.
 
But, they have their own water there, it's known for its
purpose.

53
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:18,000
O... begê siranek jî li ser hinarê tê gotin.
 
And a song is also sung about the pomegranates.

54
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:22,000
E, siran jî heye. Gî heye... E, wa! Teb'en ew jî hêle. Ew
sirane jî heye.
 
Yes, there is a song too. Everything is there... Yes, well!
Of course that also exists. That song is there too.

55
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:25,000
U alemê gî dişuxulin.
 
And everyone works.

56
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,000
Qesixiyê dikin... ezenkê xwe kom dikin, em karê gî dikin...
Karê me tenê heye.
 
They prune... they gather their wood, we do all the work...
Our work is continuous.

57
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:30,000
E neha e... li Efrînê de ... hinarê herî baş li kîjan gundê
ye?
 
So now... in Afrin... which village has the best
pomegranates?

58
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Welleh, ku em texmîn bikin... dera gî xuyî... ew Miskê naka,
dibê xin xweş e, Miskê, cem rintir, girsir dibe. Cewwê wêrê
xêr cewwê cem me ye.
 
Well, if we were to guess... everyone has their own... they
say Miske now, they say it's good, Miske, it's better there,
it gets bigger. The weather there is different from ours.

59
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,000
Ege qenaeta min ha! Cewwî wêrê xêr cewwî cem me ye.
 
That's my conviction! The weather there is different from
ours.

60
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Çi ferq heye yanî?
 
What is the difference?

61
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Cem wana bi îtibar Zeytûn dêmî ye teqrîben.
 
For them, olives are mostly rain-fed.

62
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Cem me mintaqeya me dar pir e, av pir e, retûbeyê xwe pir e.
 
For us, our region has many trees, much water, its humidity
is high.

63
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,000
U em dara jî çik-çik teng diçînin. Li wêrê dar jî fereh
çandine.
 
And we plant the trees very close together. There they plant
the trees spaced out.

64
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
Dar jî fereh çandine. Û cewwî wêrê wane ra musaede dike.
 
They plant the trees spaced out. And the weather there helps
them.

65
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Karker jî... e ... çiqas karker ba te kar diki?
 
And the workers... roughly how many workers work for you?

66
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Welleh karker... îşte em kine vedanê, me xelas kir...
qesexe.. em ke êzinga derxin.
 
Well workers... here we do the trimming, we finish it...
pruning.. we will take out the firewood.

67
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Me êzing derxistin, em ke kokê dara bi kolin paqij bikin.
 
We took out the firewood, we will dig the roots of the trees
and clean them.

68
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Em ke semet pêwerkin. Du-sê re, avdanê xwe em ke bikin.
 
We will add fertilizer. For two-three times, we will do the
watering.

69
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:25,000
Pîçka salê sê neqlan qut kin. Çewîr navde çêbû, em ke jêkin.
 
We will cut the shoots three times a year. If weeds grow in
between, we will cut them.

70
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Yanî karê me mustemir heye. Em dişuxulin.
 
So we have continuous work. We work.

71
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Spas darim te.. Spas
 
Thank you.. Thanks.

72
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,000
Keremke ehlen û sehlen..
 
You're welcome, welcome..

73
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Bêlit temaşevanan hêja.. neha em derbazî cem karkera bin.
 
Well dear viewers.. let's now go to the workers.

74
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:39,000
Ka em berin ka karker çawa kar dikin, bi gihinîke em jî fêr
bibin..
 
Let's see how the workers work, so that we can learn too..

75
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,000
Ku... karker çawa kar diki?
 
How... how the workers work?

76
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Werin keremkin.
 
Come, you're welcome.

77
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
Merheba jê ra
 
Hello to you.

78
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
Xwedê te bihêle. Sax bi.. xweştir bî.
 
May God keep you. Bless you.. be well.

79
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Em te nas bikin.
 
Let's get to know you.

80
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Navê min Celîl Birîm e.
 
My name is Celil Birim.

81
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:52,000
Ser çava.
 
On my eyes (Welcome).

82
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,000
E, tu neha darê vedidî.
 
So, you are pruning the tree now.

83
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,000
Belê erê.
 
Yes, yes.

84
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Hûn dibêjin çi?
 
What do you call it?

85
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Em dibêjin qesaxî.. ne ka gundê cem me qesaxî ye.
 
We call it pruning.. in our village it's called pruning.

86
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,000
E...
 
Yeah...

87
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:04,000
E... Ev darê hinarê ye...
 
Yeah... This is a pomegranate tree...

88
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Em ji wê re qesaxî çêdikin, bi taybet, bendûqê zêde dirêj
bûyî.
 
We prune it, especially, the shoots that have grown too
long.

89
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:12,000
Şaxê zêde di bulind bûn em qut dikin.
 
We cut the branches that have grown too high.

90
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
U heger cîk hebê, zêde paşî we siq bê..
 
And if there is a place that is too thick..

91
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
em evne ki jî nav derdixin, fehre dikin.
 
we also take out the middle, make it spacious.

92
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:21,000
U heger e... hişk tê de hebin nexweşî.. ew jêdikin...
 
And if... there are dry parts or disease in it.. we cut them
off...

93
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:26,000
jibo.. ro , ba, derîn lê.. bi hikim e ... em wiha karê xwa
dikin..
 
so that.. the sun, the wind, can pass through.. that's the
rule... this is how we do our work..

94
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Sal bi sal vedidin.
 
You prune it year by year.

95
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Belê, sal bi sal em kar dikin.
 
Yes, we work on it year by year.

96
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Neha de dê Zeytûn dibêjin.. salek e, vedi salek venadin.
 
Now for olives they say.. one year you prune, one year you
don't.

97
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
E ew zeytûn e.. em sal bi sal e. Belê.
 
Yeah that's olives.. for us it's year by year. Yes.

98
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:50,000
De ka... Keremke... Çawa kar dikî.
 
Well then... Go ahead... How do you work.

99
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
E... neha ti saetê kar dikî.
 
So... now you work by the hour.

100
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
Belê.. saet e..
 
Yes.. it's by the hour..

101
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,000
Hûn çenîk seatan kar dikin rojekê..
 
How many hours do you work a day..

102
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:57,000
Em ji sbê seat 7 diçin. Heta seat yek..
 
We go from 7 in the morning. Until one o'clock..

103
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Seat yek..
 
One o'clock..

104
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Erê ro çiqas stînî perê...
 
Yes, yes.

105
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,000
Erê ro çiqas stînî perê...
 
And how much money do you get a day...

106
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Rojî pênc hezar werqî e. .. Baş e .. ev mera jî gundê xwa da
be.
 
A day is five thousand liras. .. It's good .. this is for us
in our own village.

107
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:08,000
Û karê me ra hebê baş e.. Em gundê xwa di pênc wêraq jî
bixebitin. Jî min re 500 riyalî wane... he ev qunaeta min
heye...
 
And if we have work it's good.. Even if we work for five
liras in our own village. To me it's like 500 riyals of
theirs... yes I have this conviction...

108
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Wa ki din. Karê mera.. Gundî me ra... çêtirî wê lête
xelkiyê.. ha..
 
That's how it is. Our work.. For our village... it's better
than going to others.. right..

109
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Ti kanî me jî fêr bikî.
 
Can you teach us too.

110
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Ti fêr bikim.. belê. Çawa ka we re .. He
 
I can teach you.. yes. Here's how .. Yeah

111
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Ka... ji me re... kîjan qut bikim...
 
Show us... which one should I cut...

112
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,000
Te dît.. ewa...
 
You see.. that one...

113
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Te e... Zehmet damin... Ne ne ki qilind e..
 
You... Give me a hard time... No no it's thick..

114
00:07:44,000 --> 00:08:04,000
Erê... waha
 
Yeah... like this

115
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Merheba stêra.
 
Hello, respected one.

116
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Yaa ehlen wa sehlen.. ehlen stêra.
 
Welcome.. welcome respected one.

117
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Gundê xezewiyê mîna gelek gundên derdorê. Bûyere navdare. Û
derdora gund hemû bax...
 
The village of Ghazawiya, like many surrounding villages. It
has become famous. And the surroundings of the village are
all orchards...

118
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:31,000
û baxçeyên sebzeyan.. Û darê fêkiyan baxçê zeytûna hatiye
xemilandin.
 
and vegetable gardens. And it is decorated with fruit trees
and olive orchards.

119
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Hine malbatên gund sewalên jî xwedî dikin. Her waha, gundî
ji ber hemin çandiniyê û sewalan
 
Some families in the village also raise animals. In
addition, the villagers, from both farming and animals,

120
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:48,000
debara jiyana xwa peyda dikin. Li demên bere de kaniyêk avê
bi navê kaniya xezewiyê..
 
provide for their livelihood. In the old days, a water
spring named the Ghazawiya spring..

121
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:52,000
jêrî gund hebu. O hemû gundiyan zeviyên xwa jê avdidin..
 
was below the village. And all the villagers watered their
fields from it..

122
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Lê neha avê wê kêm buye. O gundi de avdanê da xu disipêrin
abên dawe...
 
But now its water has decreased. And the villagers rely for
watering on the water project...

123
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:07,000
bîrca Eftaloy.. ko li ser awa çemê Efrînê de di sala 1980 de
hot bû... çêkirin. Û erqên avê..
 
the Eftalo dam.. which was built on the Afrin river in 1980.
And the water channels..

124
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:27,000
li zeviyên dedore .. hatina kişandin..
 
were drawn to the surrounding fields..

125
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Birê xwatî merheba stêra..
 
Dear brother, hello respected one..

126
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
Ehlen û sehlen kî, Xudê xêra bîne, sersera herti çavaka..
 
Welcome, may God bring good, on my head and eyes..

127
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Sax bi.. îroj dera we dît wa ye.. Em hatin Xezewiyrê..
 
Bless you.. today as you see.. We came to Ghazawiya..

128
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Ya ehlen wa sehlen. Sersera her di çava.
 
Welcome. On my head and eyes.

129
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,000
e.. Ji wara jî û burinama.. bername wê axê wêlatira ji..
 
Uh.. From you too and the program.. the program of the land
of the country..

130
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
Spas dara re jî... Em dest pêk ne ew pirsin...
 
Thank you too... Let's start with this question...

131
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Nave xezewiyê jixwa hatiya..
 
Where does the name Ghazawiya come from..

132
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Nave xezewiyê kek... nav ki... Jina vê xaza ye, Xaza.
 
The name Ghazawiya brother... the name is... Its origin is
Ghaza, Ghaza.

133
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
e...
 
Yeah...

134
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Menda hatîya. Navê gundê Menda jî... ev e teqrîben dîroka
xwa vedigere nêzîka 400 sal...
 
Menda comes. The name of Menda village... its history
roughly goes back around 400 years...

135
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Pîreka ji Eşîra... yanî mezinên vir dibêjin Eşîra Şêxleran.
Pîreke wa ya mezin... navê wê Xezal bû, vir de gotin Xezû.
 
An old woman from the tribe... meaning the elders here say
