erda gund hebûn bi wê kaniyê dihatin avdan... Û gund jî, ava
xwe vexwarinê gîşt ji wir bû. Ji berî bîr tune bûn, xetas
tune bûn... îtimada xwe esasî li ser wê bîrê bûn.
 
Yes indeed, the spring... number one... the village
essentially was built on the foundation of the spring.
Therefore, however many villages there were... if there is
no spring here, no water, there was no life. Consequently,
the village spring existed, and that spring provided all the
life for the village, whatever land the village had was
irrigated by that spring... And the village too, drank its
water entirely from there. Because there were no wells
before, there were no pumps... their basic reliance was on
that well.

162
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
Kaniyek tenê ye?
 
Is it just one spring?

163
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,000
Kaniyek e... erê.
 
It's one spring... yes.

164
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Ava wê naha têde heye?
 
Does it have water in it now?

165
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:15,000
Erê... tê heye. Lê ava wê pêr daketiye... û kêm bûye.
 
Yes... there is. But its water has dropped significantly...
and decreased.

166
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,000
Ji berî pirtir bû?
 
Was it more before?

167
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,000
Na wek gundê we jî di quntara Çiyayê Lêlûn da hatiye
avakirin... Tiştekî dîrokî li dora we heye li gund da?
 
It was more before, it was a lot more.

168
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:23,000
Na wek gundê we jî di quntara Çiyayê Lêlûn da hatiye
avakirin... Tiştekî dîrokî li dora we heye li gund da?
 
No, as your village was also built at the foothills of Lêlûn
Mountain... Is there anything historical around you in the
