God bless you, and indeed, we are very grateful to you...
for your effort, and for your suffering when you reach the
history of your region, the Afrin region entirely with its
villages... for you to show it to your nation... Thank you
very much to you and to your program as well.

196
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Em jî spasiya te dikin... Û em spasiya hemû miletê me
dikin...
 
We thank you too... And we thank all our nation...

197
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Gundê Xezwê girêdayî navçeya Şêrawa ye. Kantona Efrînê, nêzî
heft kîlometreyî... li başûrê bajarê Efrînê dikeve... Di
heman demê de, yek ji gundên Deşta Cûmê ye. Li gorî gundiyan
navê gund ji navê pîrejinakê, Xezamendê hatiye. Û hin gundî
jî dibêjin... ji peyva desteser kirin, anku bi zimanê erebî
Xezwê hatiye... Hemû niştecihên gund berê Êzdî bûn. Lê piştî
dagirkeriya Osmaniyan... gelek malbat neçar man bibin
misilman... Her wiha Kurdên Êzdî... di gel kurdên
misilman... û malbateke Ereb jî di gund de, bi hevre, di
nava biratiyê... û wekheviyê de dijîn. Û di hemû çalakî... û
boneyên xelgînî û şahiyan de, xwedî li hev derdikevin. Hema
hema mirov nikare ferq û cudatiyên olî, di nav gundiyan da
nas bike.
 
Xezwê village is affiliated with the Şêrawa district. Afrin
Canton, nearly seven kilometers... to the south of Afrin
city... At the same time, it is one of the villages of the
Cûmê Plain. According to the villagers, the village's name
came from the name of an old woman, Xezamendê. And some
villagers also say... it came from the word to confiscate,
meaning in Arabic Xezwê... All the residents of the village
used to be Yazidis. But after the Ottoman occupation... many
families were forced to become Muslim... Also, Yazidi
Kurds... along with Muslim Kurds... and an Arab family in
the village too, live together, in brotherhood... and
equality. And in all activities... and occasions of sorrow
and joy, they support each other. One can hardly recognize
religious differences and distinctions among the villagers.

198
00:17:44,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Gundê Xezwê, mîna gundên din nûjen xwiya dike. Lê belê,
dîroka wê kevnar e. Lawma, gund mezin e... û nêzî sêsed û
pêncî xanî li gund heye... û sê hezar kes li gund dijîn...
Ji ber mezinihiya gund, hemû firoşgehên keleporan hene... ta
dermanfiroşek jî heye. Lewra, gundiyên hewcedariyên... ji
gundên din nabin... û hemû pêdiviyên xwe ji wan firoşgehan
peyda dikin.
 
Xezwê village, like other villages, seems modern. However,
its history is ancient. Because of this, the village is
large... and there are nearly three hundred and fifty houses
in the village... and three thousand people live in the
village... Due to the size of the village, all traditional
shops exist... even a pharmacy exists. Therefore, the
villagers don't need things... from other villages... and
they find all their necessities from those shops.

199
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Belê temaşevanan hîca, di gundê Xezwê de jî, em derbasî mala
Şêx Husên bûne.
 
Yes respected viewers, in Xezwê village too, we have entered
the house of Şêx Husên.

200
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:52,000
Sibe da jî Cejna Xidir Liyas e. Ev sê roj e milet rojî
digire... îro jî, hazirtiya xwe... Cejnê dikin.
 
Tomorrow is the Xidir Liyas Holiday. For three days the
people have been fasting... today too, they are making their
preparations... for the Holiday.

201
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:58,000
Em ê, bi hevre nas bikin dayikê em... Merheba ji we re.
 
We will, together get to know the mother... Hello to you.

202
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Ehlen wa sehlen, tu bi xêr hatî, li ser sera û ser çava.
 
Welcome, welcome, you are very welcome, upon my head and
upon my eyes.

203
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
Sax be, dayik em te nas bikin destpêkê?
 
Bless you, mother, let's get to know you first?

204
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:04,000
Ez kebaniya Şêx Husên im.
 
I am the wife of Şêx Husên.

205
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Ewê serçavê min.
 
Upon my eyes.

206
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,000
Çavê te sax bin. Ê vaye ez diqelînim... iê... îşev... iêşev.
 
May your eyes be blessed. Uh here I am roasting...
tonight... tonight.

207
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Îşev hûn amadekariya... pexûnê dikin?
 
Tonight you are preparing the... pexûn?

208
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Eh... sibe da jî cejn e. Eh...
 
Yes... and tomorrow is the holiday. Yes...

209
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:19,000
Ev gihaye... ev gihayê xaw nabe hûn bikî, nabe ku tu wisa
bikî.
 
This has reached... this cannot be made raw, you cannot do
it like that.

210
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Na. Dayê... ev e edetek kevn e...
 
No. Mother... this is an old tradition...

211
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,000
Û we pexûnê çêdikim... navê pêxûnê jê re...
 
And we make pexûn... its name is pêxûn...

212
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Yanî cejneka... bê xûn e, bê qurbanî ye.
 
Meaning it's a holiday... without blood, without sacrifice.

213
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Sal bi sal di malbata da çêdibe?
 
Does it happen year by year in the family?

214
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:41,000
Sal bi sal, bîst sal û zêde em çêdikin, bex ji Şêx Husên
rehmetî bûye, em çê nakin... ew ji du sal me çênekiribu.
 
Year by year, for twenty years and more we have been making
it, but since Şêx Husên passed away, we don't make it... for
those two years we hadn't made it.

215
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,000
Çend sale rehetî bû ye?
 
How many years has he been deceased?

216
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:48,000
Du sal e. Du sal, penc meh in. Rehma xwedê lêbe.
 
It's two years. Two years, five months. May God have mercy
on him.

217
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,000
Miriyê we jî... in.
 
Your dead too... is.

218
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:54,000
Lê dayê naha gund... çawa di van cejnan de diçin... serdana
hevdû dikin.
 
But mother now the village... how do they go during these
holidays... they visit each other.

219
00:19:54,000 --> 00:19:58,000
O, derma mala me dibe îd. Dewat e. Eger pexûnê çêbikin...
dibe dewat.
 
Oh, outside our house it becomes an eid. It's a wedding. If
they make pexûn... it becomes a wedding.

220
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Taybet... jin tên yan mêr jî tên?
 
Specifically... do women come or do men come too?

221
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Yanî berî aştan ew destare hebûn?
 
Everyone comes.

222
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
Yanî berî aştan ew destare hebûn?
 
So, before the mills, did you have these handmills?

223
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Erê me bulxur pê dihêra, û şemlûk.
 
Yes, we used to grind bulgur with it, and semolina.

224
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Me bulxur dihêra.
 
We used to grind bulgur.

225
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Berê tinebûn nok, me pê dihêra eştin me.
 
In the past there wasn't any, we used to grind our things
with it.

226
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Wele şevê şemlek me dihêra bi destar... bi destarî.
 
By God, we used to grind a sack a night with the handmill...
with the handmill.

227
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Dayê naha, kanî ji me ra bêje, hûn çi tevî hev dikin?
 
Mother, now tell us, what do you mix together?

228
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Ya genim, ton û nîveke avê din... Wele çil ton e.
 
For the wheat, it's one and a half tons for the others... By
God, it's forty tons.

229
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Çil, çil ton e.
 
Forty, it's forty tons.

230
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Kanîkê bêje... ev kî... ew çi kovar da tevlî hev e?
 
Tell us... what... what is mixed in the container?

231
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:29,000
Kî tevlî hev e? Giştîk.
 
What is mixed together? Everything.

232
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Çend ton e ev? Du ton e tevlî hev e. Du ton e.
 
How many tons is it? Two tons are mixed together. Two tons.

233
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,000
Ka ji me ra bêje.
 
Tell us.

234
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Garisê sipî heye. Ceh tê heye, genim tê heye.
 
There is white corn. There is barley in it, there is wheat
in it.

235
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:43,000
Fistiq tê hene. Baqil tê hene.
 
There are pistachios in it. There are broad beans in it.

236
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:47,000
Nok hene. Bexdenûs heye. Tirp heye.
 
There are chickpeas. There is parsley. There is radish.

237
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,000
Çil darî dermanê xwemalî heye... fistiq tê hene...
 
There are forty types of local spices... there are
pistachios in it...

238
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Baqil e, dendik e... gi heye.
 
Broad beans, seeds... there's everything.

239
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
Dendikê kundirê quste tê hene...
 
There are pumpkin seeds in it...

240
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Î dirêj tê hene, î berberok tê hene... gi heye.
 
There are the long ones in it, there are the sunflower seeds
in it... there's everything.

241
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Çend ton a dendik tenê amade kirine...
 
How many tons of just seeds do you have...

242
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:04,000
Dayê, naha her tiştê hûn dikin erdê, hûn diçînin, hûn
dikinê?
 
Mother, now everything you put in the ground, that you
plant, do you add it?

243
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:08,000
Erê, her tiştê em diçînin em dikinê, ji pişkên xwe da.
 
Yes, everything we plant we add to it, from our own shares.

244
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:13,000
Naha wek taybet... carekê ez çûm gundê Baflûnê jî min
çêkir...
 
Now, specifically... once I went to the village of Baflûn
and made a report...

245
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:14,000
Eh.
 
Yes.

246
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:16,000
Berî bi salekê wan jî bi hesabê tiştî kir...
 
A year ago, they also did something similar...

247
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:19,000
Naha pirrek dibêjin mûj jî dikeve nê. Mûj dikeve nê?
 
Now many say that raisins also go into it. Do raisins go
into it?

248
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,000
Na, mûj nakeve nê.
 
No, raisins don't go into it.

249
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:22,000
Na, em mûjan nakinê.
 
No, we don't put raisins in it.

250
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:28,000
Em bes vî tonî... berî cot, giştî dikinê.
 
We just put this ton... before plowing, we put everything
in.

251
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:29,000
Naha hûnê bidin rên?
 
Now are you going to mix it?

252
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Eh.
 
Yes.

253
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Carek din jî pirsekê... dayê merheba, stêrê re ji...
 
Once again, I ask a question... mother hello, and for the
star...

254
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Xwe ji me re nas bike.
 
Welcome.

255
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,000
Xwe ji me re nas bike.
 
Introduce yourself to us.

256
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:39,000
Ez jî bûka mala Hemîdê Qeydî me, û tev xaltiya Ofdê... keka
ezîz.
 
I am also the daughter-in-law of Hamid Qeydi's family, and
along with aunt Ofdê... dear brother.

257
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Ji berê de... ne ji nû va em çêdikin.
 
We have been making this since the past... not just
recently.

258
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:45,000
Hê, rehmetî Hemîdê Qeydî apê min ê xweş bû...
 
Yes, the late Hamid Qeydi was my beloved father-in-law
(uncle)...

259
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Û Şêx Husên hebûn...
 
And Sheikh Hussein was there...

260
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:54,000
Û me çêdikir, û wekî dît kekê ezîz me... ka ew... dore çil
tonî dikevê, pir tişt dikevê.
 
And we used to make it, and as my dear brother saw...
well... about forty tons go into it, a lot of things go into
it.

261
00:21:54,000 --> 00:22:00,000
Belkî bîst cor jê buharat a, bexdenûs e, tirp e, tiştê,
heyellah gi tişt dikevê.
 
Maybe twenty kinds of it are spices, parsley, radish,
things, by God everything goes into it.

262
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,000
Dibe bi heft ton a... tenê heft ton a tekiyê.
 
It makes about seven tons... just seven tons of seeds.

263
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Lema çi tê çandin dikevê.
 
Everything that is planted goes into it.

264
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Berê daran nakevê... erê... berê daran nakevê, bes te çi
diçînî dikevê.
 
The fruits of trees don't go in... yes... the fruits of
trees don't go in, but whatever you plant goes in.

265
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,000
Û dibe bi tarîxê... hesavê şerqî...
 
And it happens according to the date... the eastern
calendar...

266
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:19,000
Hesavê şerqî, heftê ewilî, ortê, deh-sêzdeh da, ew îda me
dibe.
 
The eastern calendar, the first week, the middle, between
the tenth and thirteenth, that is our holiday.

267
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Îda me xêr û xweşî...
 
Our holiday of goodness and joy...

268
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:26,000
Na şert e, min ortê deh-sêzdeh da...
 
It doesn't matter, in the middle of the tenth to
thirteenth...

269
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Çêdikin, û îda xwe... dêmek... xêr û xwe...
 
We make it, and our holiday... I mean... goodness and joy...

270
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:32,000
... semata xwe ya.
 
... of their "semat" (a type of traditional food or
offering).

271
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:37,000
Şûna xwînê meselen pêxûnê çêdikin û dixwin... heta sê rojan
dixwin.
 
Instead of blood, for example, they make pekhun and eat
it... they eat it for three days.

272
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Dayê ev jî... ji bo miraza ye.
 
Mother, this is also... for granting wishes.

273
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:41,000
Eh.
 
Yes.

274
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:46,000
Her kesê mirazek wî hebe... daxwazek wî hebe... vê pêxûnê
dixwe û xew dike.
 
Anyone who has a wish... who has a desire... eats this
pekhun and sleeps.

275
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,000
Eh bi xwedê, qîza min...
 
Yes, by God, my daughter...

276
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:53,000
Em di nav nekin... berî vê bi sê-çar salan xwar û xew kir.
 
Let us not hide it... three or four years ago she ate it and
slept.

277
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:58,000
Xew kir, go, anî go, min dît... pêşî mektebê go yek mirt e,
bê...
 
She slept, she said, she came and said, I saw... in front of
the school, she said, someone died, came...

278
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:02,000
Rehmetî Mehmûdê... misilman e, ji gundê Rajo bi xwe ye.
 
The late Mehmud... he is a Muslim, he's from the village of
Rajo himself.

279
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:07,000
Û qîza min rastî di Rajo di xwendê... û da mêr, neketin na!
 
And my daughter actually studied in Rajo... and gave her
hand in marriage, it didn't fail, no!

280
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Emrê wê bîst û pênc sal bûn...
 
She was twenty-five years old...

281
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:12,000
Xewna pêxûnê nabe derew e! Nabe derew e! Xewn a pêxûnê rast
e! Dicihe!
 
The dream of the pekhun cannot be false! It cannot be false!
The dream of the pekhun is true! It comes true!

282
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:14,000
Ê, qîz ka û şebaba dicihin...
 
Yes, for girls and boys it comes true...

283
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,000
Û wekî te dît... tiştê miraza dilê min sênc neba xwedê
dicirîne...
 
And as you saw... anything my heart desires, by God, it will
come true...

284
00:23:18,000 --> 00:23:22,000
Û mîna mirazê giyan... sereke... ê, mirazê şebaban û qîz
kaye.
 
And like the wishes of all... mainly... yes, it is the
wishes of the youth and girls.

285
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:25,000
Û ew jî... î giye.
 
And that is also... it's everything.

286
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,000
Û sahet û wexta we giya xwaş.
 
And may your hours and time be pleasant.

287
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,000
Taybet milleta me... êzidî dixwin, lê misilman jî dixwin?
 
Especially our people... Yazidis eat it, but do Muslims eat
it too?

288
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:36,000
Gi dixwin... gi dixwin... ebeden, na... nakin ferq. Gi
dixwin. Îslam û êzidî gi dixwin.
 
Everyone eats it... everyone eats it... never, no... they
don't differentiate. Everyone eats it. Muslims and Yazidis
all eat it.

289
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:38,000
Naha gundê we... nîvê misilman in nîvê êzidî ye.
 
Now your village... half of it is Muslim, half is Yazidi.

290
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:41,000
Gi em gi yek in.
 
All of us are one.

291
00:23:41,000 --> 00:23:43,000
Ê tiştê misilman jî tên dixwin. Û xortên misilman jî tên
dixwin.
 
The Muslims also come and eat. And the Muslim youth also
come and eat.

292
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:49,000
Gî, erê... wele wele wele... gî em gî yek in. Îslam û êzidî
gî yek in cem me.
 
All, yes... by God, by God, by God... we are all one.
Muslims and Yazidis are all one to us.

293
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:51,000
Ferqî nakin ebeden ebeden.
 
They make no difference at all, absolutely none.

294
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:53,000
Em berî de... wekî xwişk û bira kene.
 
Since the past... we are like sisters and brothers.

295
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:58,000
Wa biyek ra em cem hev in, tinne ne... tev be. Ezî misilman
im, ez êzidî me, na av yekil cem me tinne ye.
 
Like that, we are together, there isn't... no difference. I
am a Muslim, I am a Yazidi, no, that thing doesn't exist
with us.

296
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,000
Cem me tinne ye.
 
It doesn't exist with us.

297
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:04,000
Qeçkên çûk tê, mezin tê, em di navda giya da dibînin...
 
Little girls come, older ones come, we see everyone in it...

298
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:06,000
Yanî sal bi sal hûn tînin... û belav dikin... li gundî.
 
So year by year you bring it... and distribute it... to the
village.

299
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:09,000
Ê ha wa, lê em ke çi bikin... em ke belav nekin!
 
Yes, like that, what else would we do... if we didn't
distribute it!

300
00:24:09,000 --> 00:24:12,000
Tiştek malê mezin a me mezin a, em gî belav dikin.
 
It is something from a great family of ours, we distribute
it all.

301
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:15,000
Hema giyê wî hewarî didene re. Wekî dewatê dibe.
 
They just all gather around it. It becomes like a wedding.

302
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,000
Welle...
 
By God...

303
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,000
We dî dest pê kir?
 
Did you start?

304
00:24:18,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Berdê... berdê...
 
Continue... continue...

305
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,000
Ev jî bulxur e?
 
Is this also bulgur?

306
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Ev jî bulxur e, erê...
 
This is also bulgur, yes...

307
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,000
Hûn diqewrînin a destpêkê?
 
Do you roast it first?

308
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:30,000
Erê... em diqewrînin sêlekê da... û ev e...
 
Yes... we roast it on a pan... and this is it...

309
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,000
Çima paşê xwê dikinê? Noka xwê nakinê?
 
Why do they add salt later? They don't salt the chickpeas?

310
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Pêşî xwê dikine, noka xwê nakine... paşê ger... her şûnda
xwê têkine...
 
First they add salt, they don't salt the chickpeas...
then... they add salt to it later...

311
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:38,000
Sê de... şor dikin... navê xwê... pêxûn e.
 
Three times... they make it salty... the name of it... is
pekhun.

312
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:51,000
Dike pir şor bike... mela... gava bixwî... te xew da... tî
bibin, û xewna bivînin... şebabo... qîzika... mirazê kê hebe
xwedê dike... û xewna pêxûnê ne derew in!
 
They make it very salty... so when... you eat it... you
sleep... you get thirsty, and you have dreams... the
youth... the girls... whoever has a wish, God fulfills it...
and the dreams of the pekhun are not lies!

313
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,000
Dayê te jî xewn dîtî?
 
Mother, have you also seen a dream?

314
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:56,000
Na... wextê ku ez rehmetyê Şêx Husên, ez mirîdê wî. Ne.
 
No... at the time I was with the late Sheikh Hussein, I was
his disciple. No.

315
00:24:56,000 --> 00:25:00,000
Wê... ez nebûme qîza wî da min... lê min dî...
 
She... I didn't become his daughter to him... but I saw...

316
00:25:00,000 --> 00:25:01,000
Nema... wî qet ew dîtin min...
 
No... he never saw me...

317
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:06,000
Lê min dît li... me ne dît min... me hemû qebûl kir...
 
But I saw it in... we didn't see me... we accepted it all...

318
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:08,000
Yanî te Şêx Husên di xew de dîtî?
 
So you saw Sheikh Hussein in a dream?

319
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:12,000
Lê, min Şêx Husên di xew de dîtî, o... abanek dida min...
 
Yes, I saw Sheikh Hussein in a dream, he... he was giving me
a cloak...

320
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:15,000
O... û nedida wî ye ku da min...
 
And... and he wasn't giving it to him, he gave it to me...

321
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
Av jî qîza... tî mîne...
 
She is also the daughter of... my brother-in-law...

322
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Te go qîz jî gundê Xezewî ye?
 
You said the girl is also from the village of Xezewî?

323
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,000
Eh.
 
Yes.

324
00:25:20,000 --> 00:25:21,000
Wî mêrê wê heye ba won?
 
Does she have a husband there?

325
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:27,000
Xaltiya min, erebane... xaltî min... na Şêx Husên, laşê
xaltiya min bû... ah.
 
My aunt, the carriage... my aunt... no, Sheikh Hussein was
my aunt's body... ah.

326
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:29,000
Hûn û te xew dît.. we xew jî...
 
You and you had a dream... you also dreamed...

327
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:32,000
Nê... wejî tê xew nedî...
 
No... you also didn't dream...

328
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:39,000
Eger wextek di xew de... ez nebînim... ez ke tiştek bikim!
 
If sometimes in a dream... I don't see... I will do
something!

329
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:49,000
Hî da di dît da... an jî we gura xwe bikin... we ketiye...
o... xilas.
 
Yes, they saw it in it... or you should make your wish...
you fell... oh... finished.

330
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:52,000
Ka em inekî jî ji we bibêjin.. pirsîn.. spas ji te re. Te jî
xwîn xwarî di ye?
 
Let's also say something from you... asking... thank you.
Did you also eat the pekhun?

331
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,000
Erê erê.
 
Yes, yes.

332
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Berî bi çend salan?
 
How many years ago?

333
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,000
E berî naha ko çend sal, hema qîzik bûm min dî.
 
Oh, a few years ago, when I was just a young girl I saw it.

334
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:01,000
Berî naha kû sisê salî, çar salî nezanim a...
 
Before now, like three years, four years, I don't know...

335
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:06,000
Û ka xewna xwe ji me re bêje.. piştî te pêxûn xwar, û te xew
kir, te çi te xew da dî?
 
And tell us your dream... after you ate the pekhun, and you
slept, what did you see in the dream?

336
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:21,000
Min pêxûn xwar, min şî eyan dî, lawiyok li gundî me dît. Min
dî çû firnê nanê germ tanî, min dî hat, min nan ji destê
dert... min dî bir, da çû me tav da xwa nî... da xwar.
 
I ate the pekhun, I saw something clear, I saw a young man
in our village. I saw he went to the bakery to bring warm
bread, I saw him come, I took the bread from his hand... I
saw him take it, gave us water to drink... ate it.

337
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,000
Wî jî te xew da dî?
 
Did he also see you in a dream?

338
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:31,000
Ê wele nizanim wî edî mi nedî ez nizanim! Bes. Na wek wê di
xew de dî go wek eqîze xaltiya xwe ve bin... am ji gok e wa
ke lo xalti xabum.. o halas in ji.
 
Oh by God, I don't know if he saw me or not, I don't know!
Just that. No, as she saw in the dream saying they would be
like cousins (aunt's daughter)... we also said we would be
cousins (aunt's son)... and finished too.

339
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,000
Xwedê weşa vira bê le...
 
May God be with you there...

340
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:36,000
Sax bî xwedê te re ve, we jî bele.
 
May you be healthy, may God be with you, you too.

341
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:42,000
Xwedê xêra her sa war ba. De me pêxûnê çêdikin, vira meradê
qîzek lab ka giyê ve bîne.
 
May God reward everyone. When they make the pekhun, they
grant the wishes of the girls and boys to bring everything.

342
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:44,000
Ê cejna we jî pîroz be.
 
And happy holidays to you too.

343
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:46,000
Te jî pîroz be.
 
Happy holidays to you too.

344
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:52,000
As hûn jî keçek gundine.. wajî hûn te nik destarê rûniştin
e... ew êk ciwan, we çima sitarin arû? Hûn sal bi sal tên...
hûn destarê dêr in?
 
As you are also a girl of the village... you also came and
sat by the handmill... a young person, why are you sitting?
Do you come year by year... do you grind the handmill?

345
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:58,000
Erê em sal bi sal çêdikin e her ni cejna Kurdan e
êzidiyan...
 
Yes, we make it year by year, every time it's the holiday of
the Kurds, of the Yazidis...

346
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:05,000
Sal bi sal a em çêdikin em ka çikin? Tine.. ev car e em
ronin.. em çikin...
 
We make it year by year, what should we do? There is
nothing... this time we sit... what should we do...

347
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:15,000
Û her kes merazê dilê xwe de heye.. ew e bibin... û de xon û
xew dikin. De xon û xew de kon û xew axwa di vîn.
 
And everyone has a wish in their heart... that they get...
and they eat and sleep. They eat and sleep and they see
their dreams.

348
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:19,000
Ez ji divê jim inşallah... her kesê mirazê xwe gîne...
 
I also must say, God willing... everyone gets their wish...

349
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:22,000
Yanî miraz, ne bes zewacî ye.
 
I mean, a wish isn't only for marriage.

350
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:25,000
E kesê di xerîbiyê va, gari walatê xwa.
 
For the person in exile, to return to their country.

351
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,000
Î nexwaş... sax bibe.
 
For the sick... to become healthy.

352
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,000
Ê kesê zindano da e.. derê.
 
For the person in prison... to get out.

353
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:34,000
Û am jî spasî we dikin.
 
And we also thank you.

354
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:39,000
Di gundê Xezwê de komaka kavande bi navê Koma Zîlan heye...
 
In the village of Xezwe, there is an old group named Koma
Zilan...

355
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:44,000
Ji sala 1999'da... ta naha karê xweyî hunerî berdevam e.
 
From the year 1999... until now, their artistic work
continues.

356
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:52,000
Di şahî û boneyên neteweyî û olî, derdikevin ser dîkê û
berhemên xwe pêşkêş dikin.
 
In national and religious celebrations and events, they
appear on stage and present their performances.

357
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:58,000
Di rojhilatê... çiyayê Lêlûn e. Li bakur... çemê Efrînê û
gundê Keferzîtê.
 
In the east... is the Lêlûn mountain. In the north... is the
Afrin river and the village of Keferzît.

358
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:03,000
Li rojava, gundê Şadêrê û Îska... li başûr, gundê Dêr Siman.
 
In the west, the villages of Şadêr and Îska... in the south,
the village of Dêr Siman.

359
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:16,000
Gelek rewşenbîr şukand hene... ji bijîşk, dermanfiroş,
parêzer, endazyar, mamoste, û gelek kesên ku zanîngeh
qedandine hene.
 
There are many intellectuals and experts... from doctors,
pharmacists, lawyers, engineers, teachers, and many people
who have graduated from universities.

360
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

361
00:28:17,000 --> 00:28:18,000
Ehlen we sehlen.
 
Welcome.

362
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,000
Em we nas bikin destpêkê?
 
Can we get to know you first?

363
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:22,000
Seyid Elî Firas Omer. Serçava.
 
Seyid Eli Firas Omer. Upon my eyes (You're welcome).

364
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:24,000
Nûrî Menan Hebîb. Serçava.
 
Nuri Menan Habib. Upon my eyes.

365
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,000
Şêx Bedrî.
 
Sheikh Bedri.

366
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:28,000
Xelîl Menan Hebîb.
 
Xelil Menan Habib.

367
00:28:28,000 --> 00:28:30,000
Sîn Ado.
 
Sin Ado.

368
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:36,000
Mamoste, em destpêkê ji te dipirsin... te behsê kir, ku weku
ev odeya... a mêvana ye.
 
Teacher, let's ask you first... you mentioned that this is a
guest room.

369
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:37,000
Belê.
 
Yes.

370
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:40,000
Ev ode kê girt? Û ji çiqa sal da ye?
 
Who built this room? And how many years ago?

371
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:45,000
Ev ode ta wek kevintir a vê mentîqê de ye... di devera
çiyayê Kurmênc de ta wek kevintir e.
 
This room is considered the oldest in this area... in the
region of Mount Kurmênc, it's considered the oldest.

372
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:49,000
Oda mêvanê vê gundî re ye û gundên der û dorê me giş dahatin
vir...
 
It is the guest room for this village, and all the villages
around us used to come here...

373
00:28:49,000 --> 00:28:54,000
Û tiştê terîqî bibêjim... dîroka ev gundî... kurek a em
dizanin di sed û sê sed sal heye.
 
And if I speak historically... the history of this
village... a boy knows it has been here for two hundred to
three hundred years.

374
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:58,000
Ji wê bêtir... eh ez nizanim dsê sed û sê sal vir ve jîtî
ye.
 
More than that... uh, I don't know, it's been alive for
about three hundred and three years.

375
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:03,000
Çi firaxiya gund hebe, çi şahiyên gund hebûn, giş dihatin
evê derê... wekê reşt... wekî civat...
 
Whatever village gathering there was, whatever village
celebrations there were, they all came to this place... like
a council... like a meeting...

376
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Cî... diyar dibû, wez dihatin dirûniştin, ha dihatin ew ro
em rûdinin em civata xwe dikin...
 
The place... was known, they would come and sit, they would
come today we sit, we have our council...

377
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Vê hewşê da wî cemaatê... vê mezelê... vê malê da be... û
vira ji mezelê Şêx Fedîn heye, ew qal keyme!
 
In this courtyard, their gathering... this tomb... was in
this house... and here there is also the tomb of Sheikh
Fedin, that is our ancestor.

378
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:22,000
Esasê mentîqê gund em bo fir vaşartin... di vê xanî da ye.
Heta roja îro her ku... ev herêma me da... eger yek nexweş
dibe... jinik mezar nabînin... in... çavên ku nexweşikeke ji
her aliyan tînin... tînin vî mezeli vî ojixî.
 
The foundation of the village region and until here, the
condition is in this house. Until this day, around our
region, if someone gets sick, a woman doesn't see a grave,
eh, eyes that get sick, they bring women from everywhere,
they bring them to this tomb... in front of the hearth
(ojax).

379
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:27,000
Rojê dido sisê radizanin... inşallah bi emrê xwedê gişî
şîfayek a çê dibe.
 
A day, two, three... God willing, by God's command, a
healing happens.

380
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:29,000
Belê yanê te gişt dît in ew?
 
Yes, so you have seen all of this?

381
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:30,000
Erê min gişt dîtin.
 
Yes, I have seen all of it.

382
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:34,000
E kî dawiye hatî vir... o nexweş bû, û reheb bû û çû...?
 
And who came here last and was sick, and got well and left?

383
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:41,000
Canê... welleh eh her cî pir tînin asan ne... ne ew uçaq e,
am jî gar eva ken... ew nabes roja di gundê me re we toprakî
Afrînê gi raye heye.
 
My dear... by God, they bring many here, it's not easy... it
is that hearth (ojax), we also see it... it's not just the
village of ours, all of Afrin's soil has an impact here.

384
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:50,000
Kî te ev xerîb ew... am pirsa nedikin u ki ne bele.. ki hata
ehl e sena.. a wî di vîn nedari ne tabarkê xu de dî din na
ca le va kase. Uda de ram.. pirs nekir e kîne be le.
 
Who comes, they are strangers... we do not ask who they
are... whoever comes, hello and welcome. They see it, they
give their blessings... the place for people. I wouldn't go
out and ask who they are, no.

385
00:29:50,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Ojax e, ocaxa me ke devime.. e kaven hêre ha nav û babî evî
bo wî ewî. Bîrka wî hat dî, ebera de bî mî.
 
It is an ojax, an old ojax of ours... they brought it here
for the sake of the father and grandfather. Their memory was
seen, they gave respect to us.

386
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:04,000
Wekî din te çi şexs, wekî boran, yan nexweş hatine, wekî çi
te dîtin?
 
What else have you seen regarding people, like those having
seizures or the sick coming there?

387
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:10,000
Weleh dîtine... nexweş.. wek boran, dîtine tê de... wekî
gund dîtine wê de..
 
Well, we've seen it... the sick... like those having
seizures, we've seen it there... we saw the village like
that...

388
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:16,000
Jin û zarok bûn xelk me dît tê de çêdibûn.
 
Women and children, we saw people there being healed.

389
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Mamoste de destpêkê te tiştek bas kir... te got miletê me
we... Êzidî jî tê da ne... Misilman jî tê da bûn?
 
Teacher, at the beginning you mentioned something... you
said our people... Yazidis were among them... and Muslims
too?

390
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:30,000
Na Misilman, Êzidî jî dihatin. Ne bes wisa, li gorî qenatê
însan û îmana wî bû... Êzidî dihatin, Misilman dihatin, heta
fileh jî dihatin.
 
No, both Muslims and Yazidis came. It was not just that, it
was according to a person's faith and belief... Yazidis
came, Muslims came, even Christians came.

391
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Û bi bereketek... mantiqê gundan ji hemûyan marûf e ev gundê
me. Vî gundê xwe, gundê Şerfedîn e, marûfe vî mantiqê giştî
de.
 
And with blessings... our village is well-known in all the
village areas. This village of ours, the village of
Şerfedîn, is well-known in this whole region.

392
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:49,000
Berê da jî gava çi dawet çêdibûn, çi ferah dîtiban, li wî
gundî, hemu kes wira kom dibûn... ferha xwe gişt wêderê
derbas dikirin.
 
Even in the past, whenever there were weddings, whenever
there was joy in that village, everyone would gather
there... they would spend all their joy there.

393
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,000
Te wekî din tiştî ser dizanî, ser wê derê?
 
Did you know anything else about that place?

394
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:59,000
Weleh ez dizanim ew gundê Şerfedîn... ew gund berê di malê
misilmanan bû. Û gundekî kevn e ve.
 
Well, I know that the village of Şerfedîn... there, in the
past it belonged to Muslims. And it is an old village.

395
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:13,000
Û demê berê mezar hebû... roja înê xweş dibû.. datanîn wî...
gundên derdorê şêx radibûn... rojek wek dawetan çê dibûn
diçûn... bi xêr dihatin derbas dibûn... xêrek çê dibûn da
diçûn...
 
And in the past it was a shrine... Fridays were beautiful...
they would place things... the sheikhs from surrounding
villages would gather... they would have celebrations like
weddings and then leave... they came for blessings and
passed by... received a blessing and then left...

396
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,000
Xanek li gundê we hebû? Wê behsa xanek dikirin?
 
Was there a khan in your village? Were they talking about a
khan?

397
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:20,000
Xan li wê derê, li ortê gundê me bû, ortê camiya Şerfedînê.
 
The khan was there, in the middle of our village, by the
Şerfedîn mosque.

398
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,000
Kerem ke ew xanî çiye?
 
Go ahead, what kind of khan was it?

399
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:36,000
Ew xanî, wextî berê, erebe tine bûn... bi hêştir dihatin. Ji
Qerexanê heta vê derê dihatin. Heta vê derê ra diçûn wê derê
bar datanîn, wa der wê heta berbangê dadigirtin diçûna
Helebê.
 
That khan, in the past, there were no cars... they came with
camels. They would come from Qerexan up to here. They would
travel up to here, drop off their goods, and there they
would load up at dawn and head to Aleppo.

400
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:39,000
Di wê navberê de ye? Nave Qerexanê û Helebê?
 
Is it in between that area? Between Qerexan and Aleppo?

401
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:42,000
Di navbera Helebê de ye... ortê Helebê û Qerexanê ye.
 
It's between Aleppo... it's halfway between Aleppo and
Qerexan.

402
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:50,000
Bazirgan dihatin, pir dihatin. Ji ku derê bûna da dihatin.
Li vê derê xew dikirn... wêder dima heta berbangê...
berbangê jî radibûn bar dikirin, diçûna Helebê.
 
Merchants would come, many of them. Wherever they were from,
they would come. They would sleep here... stay there until
dawn... and at dawn they would pack up and go to Aleppo.

403
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,000
Tê bîra te ew tişt?
 
Do you remember those things?

404
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:55,000
Na min nedî, yê mezinan me re gotin, bapîrê me digotin.
 
No, I didn't see it, the elders told us, our grandfather
told us.

405
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,000
Ew çiqas sal ye?
 
How many years ago was that?

406
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:04,000
Wele e... bavî min heta node sal e yan sed salî bû... ewî me
re digot...
 
Well... my father was up to ninety or a hundred years old...
he used to tell us...

407
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:16,000
Wextê dihatin... masî datanîn wira, em ko biçûk bûn..
nikanî.. em wilo... me pisîk wê derê dikirin hindir, wextê
pisîk masî derdixist, me ji destê wî distend..
 
When they came... they used to put fish there, when we were
little... we couldn't get it... so we... we would send a cat
inside there, and when the cat brought out a fish, we would
take it from its paws..

408
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:17,000
Çend devê wî yî?
 
How many entrances did it have?

409
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:23,000
Çar devê wî yî.
 
It had four entrances.

410
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:25,000
Ew xan niha nema ye xirab e?
 
Is that khan no longer there, is it ruined?

411
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:29,000
Xan nema ye xirabe... naha camî e wê derê, xanî çêkirin e..
xan nemaye. Şûnê wê dawet dibe.
 
The khan is no longer there, it's ruined... now there's a
mosque there, they built houses.. the khan is gone. It is a
place for weddings.

412
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:40,000
Şûnê dawetan e. Wê deştê jî rojan dewat dibin û bazar jî
çêdibe... roja Şemiyê bazar dibe wira.
 
It's a place for weddings. In that field, weddings are held
during the day, and markets take place... on Saturdays it
becomes a market.

413
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:45,000
Mal ava. Spas dikin.
 
Bless you. Thank you.

414
00:32:45,000 --> 00:33:05,000
Ser çavan.
 
You're welcome.

415
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:20,000
Ha were were were were were were were were were were were
were were
 
Oh come come come come come come come come come come come
come come

416
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:36,000
Kurdino wate kî dîtiye... tirkan hatine em girtine... sînorî
da dane ber xwe...
 
Oh Kurds, well, who has seen... the Turks have come and
caught us... they drove us within borders...

417
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:49,000
Kî dîtiye Kurdan wisa li çolê da... Tirk gava ku em
dibirin... mêran canê xwe dikir...
 
Who has seen the Kurds like this in the desert... When the
Turks were taking us... the men sacrificed their lives...

418
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:53,000
Girtin girtine ser sînorê me..
 
They caught us, they locked us at our borders..

419
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:59,000
Ha were were were were were were were
 
Oh come come come come come come come

420
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:10,000
Li halê me tene me, halê me wisa ye...
 
Don't look at our state, our state is like this...

421
00:35:10,000 --> 00:35:30,000
Ha were were were were were were
 
Oh come come come come come come

422
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:47,000
Zalimo wî kemal paşo yo...
 
That cruel Kemal Pasha...

423
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:57,000
Kurdino, wa zozane lo zozane...
 
O Kurds, oh it's the highlands, the highlands...

424
00:35:57,000 --> 00:36:01,000
Zozane lo zozane...
 
Highlands, oh highlands...

425
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:06,000
Kî dîtiye bi xwedê de bê duman e...
 
Who has seen it without smoke by God's will...

426
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:12,000
Belekî, de wî qet be te nabe... xiyan e...
 
It's snowy, it won't be without you... it's a betrayal...

427
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:14,000
Lê loy loy...
 
Oh loy loy...

428
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:21,000
Ew hikûmeta Tirka bi ecnebiyane ye...
 
That Turkish government is with the foreigners...

429
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:33,000
Dîdaro.. Tirk û Kurmanc, hemî me girtin dane ber qerar e..
loy loy...
 
Oh lovers.. Turks and Kurds, they caught us all and
subjected us to orders.. loy loy...

430
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:44,000
Ha were were were were were were were were were
 
Oh come come come come come come come come come

431
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:48,000
Ha were were were were...
 
Oh come come come come...

432
00:36:48,000 --> 00:37:03,000
Birîndar kir, wî dîtiye me...
 
Who is wounded, who has seen us...

433
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:17,000
Lê... ew hukumata Tirkan mar e... wê kurdan dike nav sînoran
de...
 
Oh... that Turkish government, to us... it put the Kurds
within borders...

434
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:22,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja, naha jî em derbasî mala Omer Cemîlo
bûn.
 
Yes, dear viewers, now we have moved to the house of Omer
Cemilo.

435
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:27,000
Dengbêjê nemir Hesen Rehman, hezar rahmet li gora wî be.
 
The immortal Dengbêj (singer) Hesen Rehman, a thousand
blessings on his grave.

436
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:33,000
Û hemî şehîdên me, û hemû dengbêjên me yê ku çûne.
 
And all our martyrs, and all our singers who have passed
away.

437
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:37,000
Ji we re... diyarî ye rahmetî Hesen Rehman... ronî bi gora
wî be.
 
To you... a dedication to the late Hesen Rehman... may his
grave be illuminated.

438
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:42,000
Naha em derbazî mala Omer Cemîlo bûn, em hatin û gundî û
cîranên wan jî li wira ne.
 
Now we have come to the house of Omer Cemilo, we arrived and
the villagers and their neighbors are there too.

439
00:37:42,000 --> 00:37:46,000
Em spasiya wan dikin, naha jî em ê hevjîna wî nasbikin.
 
We thank them, and now we will get to know his wife.

440
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:47,000
Dayê merheba.
 
Hello, mother.

441
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,000
Ehlen wesehlen, ser çavan.
 
Welcome, you are very welcome.

442
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,000
Em te nas bikin.
 
Let's get to know you.

443
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:52,000
Ez dika Cemîlo me.
 
I am Cemilo's mother.

444
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:54,000
Ser çavan dayê. Tu hevjîna Omer Cemîlo yî?
 
Welcome, mother. Are you Omer Cemilo's wife?

445
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,000
Yê Cemîlo e.. erê.
 
Yes, Cemilo's.. yes.

446
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:59,000
Ser çavan dayê. Çend zarokên we hene?
 
Welcome, mother. How many children do you have?

447
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:04,000
Bereket, Xwedê xêrê bide... pênc lawik, çar qîz.
 
Blessings, may God provide... five boys, four girls.

448
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:05,000
Xwedê jê re bihêle.
 
May God spare them for you.

449
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:06,000
Amin.
 
Amen.

450
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,000
Omer Cemîlo tu zane, kengî rahmetî bû?
 
Do you know when Omer Cemilo passed away?

451
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Welleh nizanim, wextî paîzê... ez nizanin dîroka wî.. hezar
û nehsad heyştê û yekê da bû.
 
Well, I don't know, during the autumn... I don't know the
exact date.. it was in nineteen eighty-one.

452
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:15,000
Hezar û nehsad û heyştê û yekê de?
 
In nineteen eighty-one?

453
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:18,000
Ê erê, rast nizanim, weha bû.
 
Yes, I don't know for sure, it was like that.

454
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Naha emrê te çiqas e dayê?
 
How old are you now, mother?

455
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:24,000
Dibe haştê û pênc, weha tiştek. We wî wextî heta we bî...
 
Maybe eighty-five, something like that. Back in that time we
were like that...

456
00:38:24,000 --> 00:38:28,000
Xwedê siheta te xweş bike, dayê. Dayê naha Omer Cemîlo...
 
May God give you good health, mother. Now, mother, Omer
Cemilo...

457
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:29,000
Omer Cemîlo..
 
Omer Cemilo..

458
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:33,000
Dengbêjekî mezin bû... Kê ji wana hez dikir? Çiqas stranan
digot?
 
He was a great Dengbêj... Who liked him? How many songs did
he sing?

459
00:38:33,000 --> 00:38:38,000
"Eyşê" jê hez dikir, "Şêx Seîd" hez dikir, "Hecî"...
 
People loved "Eyşe", they loved "Sheikh Said", "Haci"...

460
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:44,000
Wî, "Sînemê" ji xweş digot. Ê ser "Dêrsim"ê xweş digot.
 
He also sang "Sineme" beautifully. He sang about "Dersim"
beautifully.

461
00:38:44,000 --> 00:38:50,000
Ê Serdarê "Eyşê" xweş... "Şêx Seîd" xweş.. min mêrê kal
gundî dît li ser reqis dikir...
 
The leader of "Eyşe" was nice... "Sheikh Said" was nice.. I
saw an old man from the village dancing to it...

462
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:52,000
Li tembûrê jî dixist?
 
Did he play the tanbur too?

463
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:59,000
Ay wele tembûr.. bi tiliyên xwe.. wî lê dixist. Xelk hemî
dihat, bi we wilo dikirin. Xelk da wilo.. dî lê dixist
wila...
 
Oh yes, the tanbur.. with his fingers.. he played it.
Everyone would come, they would gather like that. People
were like that.. he would play it...

464
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:03,000
De wextê wî de.. kî dihat civatî wî? Kî dihat dîwanî?
 
And during his time.. who would come to his gatherings? Who
would come to the diwan?

465
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:12,000
Mêvan pir.. xelk dihat wî da civat dikirin... wext dihatin
xelk jî pey wî dihat...
 
Many guests.. people would come and form gatherings around
him... when they came, more people would follow him...

466
00:39:12,000 --> 00:39:15,000
Çar dihatin rojê, pênc dihatin.. mal tijî dibû.
 
Four would come a day, five would come.. the house was full.

467
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:23,000
Meriv bi erebeyan dihatin.. xelk dihat... ji Qamişlo dihat..
wera de hatin.. xelk dihatin tijî dibû..
 
People came in cars.. people would come... they came from
Qamishli.. they came there.. people would come and it would
be full..

468
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:27,000
Rojê deh wira bûn.. ji Efrînê, wira, ji Cinderêsê dihatin..
mal tim tijî bû.
 
Ten would be there a day.. they came from Afrin, from there,
from Jinderes.. the house was always full.

469
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:31,000
Min digot: tişt te baxça kiribû wira... min digot tişt wî
xelqê em çawa teqsîr bûn...
 
I used to say: it was like you planted a garden there... I
would tell those people, how could we fall short...

470
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:41,000
Wê te jî tembûr weke bavê xwe hilgirtiye? Weke bavê xwe.. ê
wî Omer Cemîlo... te wî wisa tembûr dî destê xwe da tu
stranan dibêjî?
 
Have you also picked up the tanbur like your father? Like
your father.. Omer Cemilo... do you also have the tanbur in
your hand and sing songs?

471
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:50,000
Wele e, tembûrê lê dixim. Kilama piçk piçk.. bes wek wî
birakî min Emer hebû...
 
Well yes, I play the tanbur. A few songs here and there..
but it was like my brother Emer...

472
00:39:50,000 --> 00:40:00,000
ne... me ew nîvî lê nedixist. Wî pir lê dixist.. min nikanî
wilo bixim...
 
no... we couldn't even play half of what he played. He
played a lot.. I couldn't play like that...

473
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:01,000
Eh... stranên te.
 
Uh... your songs.

474
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:06,000
Ew jî, yê din ji xeynî... Omer û yê din... kîjan birayê te
din?
 
Also, the other one apart from... Omer and the other...
which other brother of yours?

475
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:09,000
Kî stran... yanî wek kî dengê bavê te xera kiriye?
 
Who sings... I mean, who inherited your father's voice?

476
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:13,000
Me çi çêkiriye weleh, yanî wek din kesî deng nekiriye.
 
We haven't done much by God, meaning none of us else sang.

477
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:14,000
Xwişkeke min yek heye.
 
I have one sister.

478
00:40:14,000 --> 00:40:17,000
Mezin e, naha li gund e... wê hinekî derxistibû...
 
She is older, now she is in the village... she had picked it
up a little bit...

479
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:18,000
Li kû ye?
 
Where is she?

480
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:20,000
Mala wê li gund e weleh.
 
Her house is in the village by God.

481
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
Erê li gund e?
 
Yes, in the village?

482
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,000
Erê li gund e.
 
Yes, she is in the village.

483
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:24,000
Di gund da.
 
In the village.

484
00:40:24,000 --> 00:40:25,000
Erê, di gund da.
 
Yes, in the village.

485
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:28,000
Tu xweş dibêjî, lê ew jê xweş dibêje?
 
You sing beautifully, but does she sing better?

486
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:31,000
Weleh wê wisa... wextê berê ji min re distira...
 
By God like this... in the past she used to sing to me...

487
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Weleh naha... qirik a mezin ew bû. Deng bi wê bû.
 
By God now... she had the deep voice. She had the voice.

488
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Min qey bîr kiriya na derxim, weleh erê.
 
I think I have forgotten, I don't project it well, yes by
God.

489
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:39,000
Ê de destpêkê... na bavê te min...
 
Uh from the beginning... your father I...

490
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:41,000
Min pir guhdar kirî bavê te.
 
I listened to your father a lot.

491
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:43,000
I... ji kê fêr bû bavê te?
 
Uh... who did your father learn from?

492
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:46,000
Yanî ji malbetê, kes dengbêj hebû berê?
 
I mean from the family, was there any dengbêj before?

493
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Lê bapîrê xwe ra bû... bapîrê xwe ra deng derdixist, Ehmed
Kolo.
 
Yes, his grandfather did... his grandfather produced a
voice, Ehmed Kolo.

494
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:55,000
Dêk bû navê dêkê Kul bû.
 
There was a mother, the mother's name was Kul.

495
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:58,000
Xaltîkek xwe ra bû, navê wê Henîfe bû...
 
He had an aunt, her name was Hanifa...

496
00:40:58,000 --> 00:40:59,000
Ev gişt şêrîn bûn...
 
They all had sweet voices...

497
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:03,000
Ê... ji Bircikê me ne, nav gundê mezin de bûn, evana qey
deng derdixistin.
 
Uh... they are from our Bircik, they were in the big
village, I guess they produced a voice.

498
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,000
Bavê min jî ji bo wê fêr bû.
 
My father learned because of that too.

499
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Bavê te ne ji Xezewiyê ye?
 
Isn't your father from Xezewiyê?

500
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
Esilê min ne ji Xezewiyê ye. Dêk û navê min ji Xezewiyê ne.
 
My origin is not from Xezewiyê. My mother and my name are
from Xezewiyê.

501
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,000
Bas bavê min bi xwe jê Bircikê ye şêr e weleh.
 
But my father himself is from Bircik, brave by God.

502
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:13,000
Yanî bavê te jê Xezewiyê çawa ji, hatine virî?
 
I mean, your father from Xezewiyê how, did they come here?

503
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:16,000
Kolkê me hatine vir, kolkê me hatine vir...
 
Our grandfather came here, our grandfather came here...

504
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:17,000
Kolkê te?
 
Your grandfather?

505
00:41:17,000 --> 00:41:21,000
Erê kolkê me hatiye vir. Bavê min li vir çêbûye mesela.
 
Yes our grandfather came here. My father was born here for
example.

506
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:24,000
Bes evana yanî, ev bapîr kolkê me em gihaştine Bircikê ne...
 
But them I mean, this grandfather, our grandfather, we have
reached Bircik...

507
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:28,000
Em qalk û bavê xwe binasin em gihêştin Qasê yanî...
 
If we track our ancestors we reached Qase I mean...

508
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:36,000
Zêdetirîn kilameke ku... bavê te destira tê digirt...
 
The song that... your father sang most and you learned...

509
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:40,000
Bavê te... yanî her stranek ku te hew dikir te dihgirt.
 
Your father... I mean any song that you loved, you caught.

510
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,000
A erê weleh.
 
Oh yes by God.

511
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:45,000
Ê kîjan kilaman pir digotin? Kîjan... klamên wî...
 
Uh which songs did they sing a lot? Which... his songs...

512
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:51,000
Weleh, hasabê weqê... hatibû li cem wî dîywanê, çi kilam ceh
dixwastin... e pir Eyşê dixwastin.
 
By God, regarding the time... when people came to his
gathering, what songs did they ask for there... uh they
mostly asked for Eyşê.

513
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:56,000
Mem û Şivan dixwastin... bêm mal... ey Mohemo...
 
They asked for Mem u Şivan... come home... oh Mohemo...

514
00:41:56,000 --> 00:41:59,000
Hemiyê... evqas di xwastin... pir destira wa.
 
All of them... they wanted this much... he sang those a lot.

515
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:03,000
Kilamên xwe jî hebûn kênqa destirî? Naha nestira...
 
He also had his own songs, how much did he sing? He didn't
sing them now...

516
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:08,000
Hema yek caran hêmî derên waq pêşiya hama ev destira.
 
Usually just once in a while in front of places he would
sing these.

517
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:10,000
Bas teşcîlê derneriya nedi... ne destirî.
 
But the recording didn't come out, he didn't... he didn't
sing.

518
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:16,000
Yanî kilamên evî bavê evî bû bas ew kilamên xwa têr ne
derxistin... klom ê wî qey pir bûn.
 
I mean those songs were his father's, but he didn't put out
enough of his own songs... his songs were actually many.

519
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:19,000
E xwe ji dibê, tego dengê min li serê qopeya zer kir.
 
He also says it himself, saying my voice made the top of the
domes yellow.

520
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:22,000
Tego, a... nesîrête xwedê li wê da, ev dengê mine.
 
He said, ah... God's blessing is on it, this is my voice.

521
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:24,000
Te qet dît dema di strîya?
 
Did you ever see when he was singing?

522
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:26,000
Pê de çûk bûm le min dî weke strîye.
 
I was small but I saw when he sang.

523
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:27,000
Wê cawe dikir?
 
How did he do it?

524
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,000
A we dikir... makrafonekî wê hey bu.
 
Ah he did it like this... he had a microphone.

525
00:42:29,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Hate subê sareva destriyê.
 
Until morning he sang continuously.

526
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:35,000
Na diwêstiya û na xra di qediyê.
 
He didn't get tired and his voice didn't get ruined.

527
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:38,000
Sara va deçû...
 
He kept going continuously...

528
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:40,000
Ev e dengbêjiya resan ev e rasti yanê.
 
This is the authentic dengbêj tradition truly.

529
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:43,000
Em sîpasiya we deken.
 
We thank you.

530
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,000
Spas ji te jî.
 
Thanks to you too.

531
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:50,000
Sîpas ta jî dikim, te sere me da we ez wenê... perî dilşad
bûyîm.
 
Thanks to you too for coming, you visited us, I am... very
happy.

532
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:52,000
Kêf... a jî şad bûm.
 
Joy... I was happy too.

533
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:56,000
Em xatirê we dixwezin... eger stranek te hebê stranek din
bibêjê.
 
We say goodbye to you... if you have a song, sing another
song.

534
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:58,000
Wileh ez sîpase we dikim.
 
By God I thank you.

535
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,000
Da em bi stranekê xatirê xwa je wa baxwazin.
 
So we can say goodbye to you with a song.

536
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:06,000
Sar cava, ehlen wesehlen gorban... sere çava we hatî we xer
slamat...
 
On my eyes, welcome darling... you came on my eyes with
peace and safety...

537
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:10,000
Xate ma roneştine na qablî wan ma... xwede sîpa te xra
neke...
 
You sat with us and accepted us... may God not ruin your
thanks...

538
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:14,000
Bale tamaşevana hêca, lewercî a me xatrê xu ju we te baxwzê.
 
Yes esteemed viewers, here too we will say goodbye to you.

539
00:43:14,000 --> 00:43:18,000
A wer cê gaşt dawoye parnamê xwê, ta hefta dîn do wesa bav
raban.
 
Here it reached the end of its program, until next week we
will be together like this again.

540
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Lî ben dîtina dîn ben. Le xwaşey ben.
 
Looking forward to seeing you again. Be well.

541
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:26,000
(Singing) Lê lê lê lê lê, lê mîro...
 
(Singing) Oh oh oh oh oh, oh sir...

542
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:31,000
(Singing) De malan û milan, Esmera... de mal ava yê...
 
(Singing) Oh homes and shoulders, Esmera... oh blessed
house...

543
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:44,000
(Singing) Te go rabe sîng û berê te wekî zêr e, lê lê lê
lê...
 
(Singing) You said get up, your chest and breast are like
gold, oh oh oh oh...

544
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:50,000
(Singing) Wez ê bihar im, şaşê di milê te re ketiye...
 
(Singing) I am the spring, the scarf has fallen on your
shoulder...

545
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:59,000
(Singing) Way way way way, heval heval e, rabe dîn e...
 
(Singing) Alas alas alas alas, friend is a friend, get up
crazy one...

546
00:43:59,000 --> 00:44:06,000
(Singing) Xwedê da derda serê nexweşîyê dikire... oy oy oy
oy...
 
(Singing) God gave troubles upon the head of sickness... oh
oh oh oh...

547
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:20,000
(Singing) Way way way, rabe rabe, qedera min ev e lê lê lê
lê...
 
(Singing) Alas alas alas, get up get up, this is my fate oh
oh oh oh...

548
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:26,000
(Singing) Wez ê nizanim feleka me wê te ra xayîn e... xwedê
yo tu zanî...
 
(Singing) I do not know our fate is treacherous to you... oh
God you know...

549
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:36,000
(Singing) Bêbext e felek... feleka me wê te ra xayîn e wisa
ye...
 
(Singing) Fate is treacherous... our fate is treacherous to
you it's like that...

550
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:41,000
(Singing) Way...
 
(Singing) Alas...

